Preheat the oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4.Place all the ingredients for the crumble mixture in a large bowl.Rub the butter into the flour, sugar and salt, lifting and dropping the mixture lightly through your fingers.Pile the rhubarb into a buttered earthenware dish. Sprinkle over with the sugar, pour over the lemon juice and distribute the flakes of butter over the fruit.Cover the fruit with the crumble mixture, sprinkle over a little extra golden caster sugar. Place into the oven and bake for 35-40 minutes, or until golden on top and the jammy juices are oozing up around the edges of the dish.Serve with lovely and thick Guernsey cream.